name: Foam Roller - Adductors
description: On your stomach, slowly foam roll the length of your inner thigh. If you find a tender spot, hold for 30 seconds. Don’t have a foam roller? You can use a tennis ball or water bottle.

name: Foam Roller - Calves
description: Slowly roll the length of your calf. If you find a tender spot, hold for 30 seconds. Don’t have a foam roller? You can use a tennis ball or water bottle.

name: Foam Roller - Hamstrings
description: Place foam roller just before the glute & roll the length of your hamstring. If you find a tender spot, hold for 30 seconds. Don’t have a foam roller? You can use a tennis ball or water bottle.

name: Foam Roller - IT-Band
description: On your side, slowly foam roll from the outer hip joint down toward the knee. If you find a tender spot, hold for 30 seconds. Don’t have a foam roller? You can use a tennis ball or water bottle.

name: Hip Flexor Static Stretch (Standing)
description: Stand with one leg in front of the other. Raise the arm that is on the same side as your back leg, engaging your core as you lean backward until a stretch is felt in your hip. Rotate the shoulder of your raised arm back to deepen the stretch.

name: Calves Static Stretch
description: Stand about three feet from a wall and put one foot behind you, ensuring your toes are facing forward. Keep your heel on the ground and place your hands on the wall, bending your front leg and keeping your back leg straight.

name: Adductors Static Stretch
description: Begin in a wide-leg stance with toes pointing straight. Bend one leg and shift the hips toward that side.

name: Hamstrings Static Stretch
description: Begin on your back with your legs on the floor. Bring one knee towards your chest and slowly straighten your lower leg. Keep a firm hold on the back of your leg as your pull it toward you to deepen the stretch.

name: Hip Bridge (double leg)
description: Begin on your back with your knees bent and your feet flat on the floor, shoulder-width apart. Squeeze your glutes and lift your hips off the floor to a flat-back position. Hold for 1-2 seconds, then relax and bring your hips back to the ground. Repeat for recommended reps.

name: Single Leg Balance (multiplanar) with Reach
description: Stand with your hands on your hips and feet shoulder-width a part. Engage your core and glutes as you take one leg and reach forward, tapping your foot on the ground in front of you. Move back to the starting position. Next, reach out to the side with the same leg, maintaining the alignment of your other knee and continuing to engage your core and glutes. Move back to the starting position. Finish by reaching behind your body with the same leg.

name: Double Leg Squat (Bodyweight)
description: Stand with your feet shoulder width apart, toes pointing forward, and arms where they are comfortable. Bend your knees and sit back with your hips as if into a chair. As you squat, maintain balance by looking forward and keeping your chest up. Straighten up once maximum depth is reached. Repeat for recommended reps.

name: Soleus Static Stretch
description: Stand about three feet from a wall and put one foot behind you, ensuring your toes are facing forward. Keep your heel on the ground and place your hands on the wall, bending your front leg. Once in this position, bend your back knee but do not let your heel come off the ground. You should feel a stretch deeper in your calf.

name: Standing TFL Static Stretch
description: Begin in a standing position with your toes pointing forward. Turn one foot to the outisde. With the opposite foot step forward into a lunge position, keeping your hips facing the front. Place your hands on your hips for balance.

name: Ankle Dorsiflexion
description: Begin seated on the floor with your legs extended, toes facing up. Bring your toes towards you, holding for 1-2 seconds. Relax back to a neutral position.

name: Single - Leg Calf Raise
description: Begin on an elevated surface (i.e. stair/step) with heels hanging off. Lift one leg off the ground (place hands on nearby wall for support). Push onto toes of the other leg and hold for 1-2 seconds. Lower heel back down beyond level of surface to stretch the calf.

name: Foam Roller - Piriformis
description: Sit on top of a foam roller. Bring one ankle to the opposite knee. Shift your weight to the same side as the crossed leg, rolling over the buttocks until you feel tension in your upper glute. Hold for 30 seconds. Switch sides and repeat. Don’t have a foam roller? You can use a tennis ball or water bottle.

name: Supine Piriformis Static Stretch
description: Begin lying on the floor with both legs extended. Bring your ankle to the opposite knee to assume a "Figure-4" position. Pull the raised leg towards your chest until the stretch is felt through the upper hamstring and glute. Hold stretch for 30 seconds.

name: Foam Roller Quadriceps
description: Begin on your stomach with a foam roller beneath one thigh. Keeping that foot off of the ground, shift your weight onto that leg as you roll the length of the muscle from the knee to the hip, holding points of tension for 30 seconds. Switch sides and repeat. Don’t have a foam roller? You can use a tennis ball or water bottle.

name: Kneeling Hip Flexor Static Stretch
description: Begin in a lunge with your back knee and your front foot on the floor. Shift your weight forward, keeping your hips facing the front until you feel a stretch in your hip and hold for 30 seconds.

name: Quadruped Arm/Opposite Leg Raise
description: Begin on your hands and knees with your back flat. Simultaneously raise the right arm and left leg until the extended arm and leg are horizontal. Hold for 1-2 seconds, then bring your arm and leg back down. Alternate sides as you complete the set number of reps.

name: Floor Prone Cobra
description: Begin on your stomach with your arms by your sides. Lift your shoulders and chest off the floor, pinching your shoulder blades together. Keep your neck in line with your spine. Release back down to the floor.

name: Towel scrunches (Intrinsic Foot Muscles)
description: Begin with your feet resting on a towel, flat on the floor. Draw the towel towards you by scrunching your toes. Keep heels in contact with the floor throughout.

name: Foam Roller - Hip Flexor
description: Begin on your stomach and place a ball or foam roller beneath one hip. Keeping that foot off of the ground, shift as much weight onto the leg to be rolled as is tolerable, roll along the hip region, holding points of tension for 30 seconds. Switch sides and repeat. Don’t have a foam roller? You can use a tennis ball or water bottle.

name: Foam Roller - Latissimus Dorsi
description: Lie on one side with the arm on the ground over your head with thumb facing upwards. Place a foam roller under the arm. Slowly roll down your side back and forth. If you find a tender spot, hold for 30 seconds. Repeat on other side. Don’t have a foam roller? You can use a tennis ball or water bottle.

name: Erector Spinal Static Stretch
description: Begin seated with legs extended in front of you. Cross one leg over the other and place that foot on the other side of the extended leg. Place your elbow on the outside of the bent knee and your other hand on the floor for support. Move into a twist and push your elbow into your knee to deepen the twist. Hold for 30 seconds, then repeat the stretch on the other side.

name: Latissimus Dorsi Static Stretch
description: Kneel in front of a chair, ball, or foam roller and place one arm on top of the object with your thumb pointed up toward the ceiling. Keep the other hand on the ground. Lower your hips back toward your heels until a stretch is felt alongside the torso.

name: Isometric Ankle Dorsiflexion
description: Begin seated on the floor or in a chair. Bring one ankle to the opposite knee. Grasp the toes and pull your toes up, feeling a stretch through the back of your leg and foot. Hold for 15 seconds, then relax. Repeat on the other foot.

name: Isometric Ankle Plantarflexion
display_name: Ankle Stretch and Hold (Away From You)
description: Begin seated on the floor or in a chair. Bring one ankle to the opposite knee. Grasp the toes and pull your toes down, feeling a stretch through the front of your ankle. Hold for 15 seconds, then relax. Repeat on the other foot.

name: Ankle Inversion
description: Begin seated with your legs extended. Keeping your lower leg stable, point your toes in toward your midline. All of your motion should be coming from your ankle. Complete for the recommended number of reps on both feet.

name: Ankle Eversion
description: Begin seated with your legs extended. Keeping your lower leg stable, point your toes out away from your midline. All of your motion should be coming from your ankle. Complete for the recommended number of reps on both feet.

name: Ankle Dorsiflexion and Eversion
description: Begin seated with your legs extended. Keeping your lower leg stable, point your toes up and out, away from your midline. All of your motion should be coming from your ankle. Complete for the recommended number of reps on both feet.

name: Ankle Plantarflexion and Inversion
description: Begin seated with your legs extended. Keeping your lower leg stable, point your toes down and in toward your midline. All of your motion should be coming from your ankle. Complete for the recommended number of reps on both feet.

name: Double Leg Calf Raise
description: Stand with both feet flat on the ground and legs shoulder width apart. Lift your heels by pressing up through your toes and contracting your calf muscles. Slowly lower your heels to the neutral starting position.

name: Double Leg (up); Single leg (down) calf raise
display_name: Double Leg (Up) - Single Leg (Down) Calf Raise
description: Begin on an elevated surface (ie. stair/step) with heels hanging off. Push onto toes with both legs, then lift one leg off the ground. With control, lower the other heel back down to the level of the surface.

name: Foam Roller - Peroneals
description: Lay on your side with a foam roller under your lower leg. Support your weight on your forearm as you raise your hips off the ground. Roll the side of your lower leg, from below the knee to above the ankle, pausing at points of tenderness. Repeat on the other leg. Don’t have a foam roller? You can use a tennis ball or water bottle.

name: Foam Roller - Tibialis Anterior
description: Lay on your side with a foam roller under your lower leg. Support your weight on your forearm as you raise your hips off the ground. Roll back and forth over the outside portion of your lower leg. Hold tender areas for about 30 seconds or until discomfort decreases. To increase pressure, stack one leg on top of the other and roll the bottom leg. Don’t have a foam roller? You can use a tennis ball or water bottle.

name: Foam Roller - Tibialis Posterior
description: Lie on your stomach and place roller on the inside portion of your shin. Slowly roll the inner shin to find a tender spot. Hold for 30 seconds. Repeat on the other side. Don’t have a foam roller? You can use a tennis ball or water bottle.

name: Foam Roller- Bottom of Foot
description: Start off standing (can be performed seated) with shoes off. Place the arch of your foot on a foam roller or ball. Press down firmly, rolling across the arch of your foot. Continue for 10-30 seconds, and then switch to the other foot. Don’t have a foam roller? You can use a tennis ball or water bottle.

name: Toe Lifts
description: Stand with your feet shoulder width apart and weight balanced across your foot. Lift your toes upward toward your shins, keeping your heels on the ground. Hold briefly at the top, then slowly let your toes return to the ground.

name: Calf Raise on Raised Surface
description: Stand on the edge of an elevated surface, feet shoulder-width apart and heels hanging off. Use the wall or a rail as a support to stay balanced. Push up onto your toes so your heels raise up, pause, then lower yourself back to the starting position.

name: Posterior Pelvic Tilt
description: Lie on your back with the knees bent and the soles of the feet on the floor. On an exhale, contract your abdomen to round your back so it is flush against the ground. Your hips should not leave the floor. Hold for 1-2 seconds, maintaining the abdominal contraction, then relax.

name: Bent Knee Hip External Rotation (On Side)
description: Begin by lying on your side with your legs stacked and knees bent. Open the top hip, lifting your knee away from your body. Maintain contact between your feet throughout the movement. Pause at the top of the motion, and then return to the starting position.

name: Supine Arm/Leg Raise - Dying Bugs
description: Lie on your back with your legs straight and your arms overhead. Bend your hips and knees. Contract your abdomen so your low back is flush with the ground. Move one leg and the opposite arm to the ground, straightening the knee and hip to bring the leg just above the ground. Engage your core and return the working limbs to the starting position.

name: Cobra Abdominal Stretch
description: Lie face down with your hands under your shoulders. Slowly push your torso up as far as you comfortably can – try to get your hips to rise off the floor slightly.

name: Foam Roller - Erector Spinae
description: Place a foam roller behind your low back. Cross your arms in front of you and protract your shoulders. Raise your hips off of the floor and lean back, keeping your weight on your lower back. Roll over your back, holding points of tension for 30 seconds. Repeat on the other side. Don’t have a foam roller? You can use a tennis ball or water bottle.

name: Child's Pose Arms Straight
description: Begin on your hands and knees with your hands shoulder-width apart, and back flat (spine neutral). Sit back onto your heels and allow your body to come to the ground with your arms outstretched. Breathe deeply and hold for 30 seconds.

name: Child's Pose to Side
description: Begin on your hands and knees with your hands shoulder-width apart, and back flat (spine neutral). Sit back onto your heels and allow your body to come to the ground with your arms outstretched. Take your arms and reach to one side, lengthening through the opposite side.

name: 4-Way Ankle Mobility
description: This exercise will be performed in 4 directions for the assigned number of reps. First, point your toes straight down as far as you are able. Next, pull your toes up toward you. Third, keep your lower leg stable as you point your toes in. Finish by pointing your toes out.

name: 4-Way Ankle Isometrics (Towel)
description: This exercise will be performed in 4 different directions. First, loop the towel around your foot, grasping the ends in your hands. Push your foot down against resistance, but do not allow your foot to move. Next, angle your pull away from you and push your toes in toward your midline. Third, angle your pull toward your midline and push your toes out against resistance. Finally, loop the towel around the uninvolved foot and pull up against resistance.

name: Standing Quads Stretch
description: Stand tall, holding onto a chair or wall for balance if necessary (not pictured). Keep your feet hip-width apart, your back straight and your feet parallel. Reach back and grab your left foot in your left hand, keeping your thighs lined up next to each other and left leg in line with the hip.

name: Dynamic Runner Lunges
description: Stand with your feet together and hands at your waist. Take a big step forward and bend your legs to form 90 degree angles. Once in your lunge, try a few pulses. Then, straighten your legs back up and repeat, alternating sides.

name: Seated Forward Fold
description: Begin seated with your legs outstretched. Bending from the waist, reach forward as far as you are able.

name: Lateral Hip Openers
description: Stand in a wide-stance with your hands on your hips. Lower into the stretch by shifting your weight to one side in a lateral lunge. Come back to the neutral position and repeat on the other side.

name: Foam Roller - Levator Scapulae
description: Stand with your back against a wall. Place a ball between the wall and the back of your neck, just off center. If you feel have any points of tenderness, you may place the ball over those. Keeping the ball in contact with the wall, bend and rotate your neck so you are looking down toward your opposite front hip. Use you hand to push on the back of your head for more of a stretch.

name: Foam Roller - Upper Trapezius
description: Stand with your back against a wall. Place a ball between the wall and on your upper back, in between your shoulder and neck. If you feel have any points of tenderness in this area, you may place the ball over those. Keeping the ball in contact with the wall, push your thumb into the muscle from the front. Bend your neck as far as you can and look straight down.

name: Upper Trap Static Stretch
description: Place your hands on the back of your head and pull your head down. Make sure you do not round through your back as you pull.

name: SCM Static Stretch
description: In a seated position, place one hand under your leg to keep your shoulder level during the stretch. Bring the other hand to the opposite side of your head and pull your head to the side. Try to get your ear as close to your shoulder without lifting the other shoulder.

name: Cervical Rotator Static Stretch
description: In a seated position, sit on one hand to keep your shoulder level during the stretch. Bring the other hand to the opposite side of your head and pull your head to the side. Try to get your ear as close to your shoulder without lifting it.

name: Posterior Deltoid Static Stretch
description: Stand feet shoulder-width apart and cross one arm over your body at chest-level. Apply pressure on your forearm with your other hand to stretch the back of your shoulder.

name: Cervical Flexion/Extension
description: Stand feet shoulder-width apart. Keeping your shoulders level and your back straight, bend your head forward so you are looking down at your toes. Then, extend your neck all the way up so you are looking at the ceiling. This is one rep. Repeat for the recommended number of reps.

name: Cervical Sidebending
description: Stand feet shoulder-width apart. Keeping your shoulders level and your back straight, bend your head to the side, bringing your ear as close to your shoulder as you can. Then, bend your head to the other side. This is one rep. Repeat for the recommended number of reps.

name: Cervical Rotation
description: Stand feet shoulder-width apart. Keeping your shoulders level and your back straight, look over one shoulder as far as you can without moving your torso or hips. Then, look over your other shoulder. This is one rep. Repeat for the recommended number of reps.

name: Cervical Retraction
description: Stand feet shoulder-width apart. Keep your shoulders level and your back straight. Scoop your chin down and back so you are tucking it back and elongating your neck. Hold the tucked position for 1-2 seconds, then release. Repeat for the recommended number of reps.

name: Scapular Retraction
description: Stand feet shoulder-width apart. Keep your shoulders level and your back straight. Scoop your chin down and back so you are tucking it toward the back of your neck. Hold the tucked position for 1-2 seconds, then release. Repeat for the recommended number of reps.

name: Lower Trapezius Prone Floor Scaption
description: Lay on the floor on your stomach. Extend your arms so they are above your head on the ground. With your thumb pointing toward the ceiling, lift your arms off the ground and hold for 1-2 seconds. Make sure your chest maintains contact with the ground. Relax your arms back to the ground. Repeat for the recommended number of reps.

name: Scapular Elevation
description: Sit or stand with your shoulders level and your back straight. Bring your shoulders up into shrug, bringing them as close to your ears as you can. Relax and let your shoulders fall back to the starting position. Repeat for the recommended number of reps.

name: Walking Hamstring Scoops
description: Step forward and straighten your leg, lifting your toes off the ground as you lean down, moving your arms in a scooping motion. Straighten back up and repeat on the other leg as you take another step forward.

name: Knee Hug to Lunge with Reach
display_name: Knee Hug to Lunge with Reach
description: In a standing position, bring your knee to your chest and wrap your hands around your shin to pull your knee farther up. Release that leg and step it forward, dropping into a lunge. Reach the opposite arm up and over the head to stretch the hip. Push up to standing with the back leg, then repeat on the other side.

name: Walking Superman
description: Take a step then lean forward, bring the back leg off the ground. Extend your arms out in front of you, making a straight line from your hands down to the foot off the ground. Stand back up and take a step forward with the leg that was raised, and repeat.

name: Hurdle Walks (In)
description: Standing in place, bring your knee out and move it in toward your midline to "close" your hips. Complete for the set number of reps.

name: Hurdle Walks (Out)
description: Standing in place, bring your knee up and move it out away from your midline to "open" your hips. Complete for the set number of reps.

name: Iron Cross
description: Laying on your back with your arms in a T-position, bring one leg up toward the opposite arm as far as you can without lifting your midback off the ground. Bring that leg back down to the starting position, then repeat on the other side. Complete for the set number of reps.

name: Mini Skips
description: Skip with minimal movement, keeping your steps small and jump height relatively low.

name: Skips for Height
description: Skip to reach maximal height, driving one knee and your opposite arm into the air at the same time.

name: Butt Kicks
description: In a standing position, flex your knee to kick your heel up to your glute. Repeat this motion, alternating each leg and moving at a quick pace.

name: Lateral Shuffles
description: Stand feet shoulder-width apart, knees and hips bent in a half-squat position. Shuffle your feet to one side, taking 4 steps before coming to a stop. Shuffle back in the opposite direction. This is one rep. Be sure to stay squatted throughout the entire movement. Complete for the designated reps.

name: Carioca
description: Standing feet shoulder-width apart, cross one leg over the other. Next, step your back foot out so you are in the starting position. Cross the first foot behind your other foot. Step the front foot out to be back in the starting position. Repeat this motion quickly, then perform the exercise again in the other direction.

name: Backward Run
description: Stand feet shoulder-width apart. Jog backward the designated distance, then turn around and jog backward to the starting point.

name: High Knees
description: Jog in place, driving your knees high into the air with every step.

name: Leg Swings
description: Use a wall for support if needed. Keep your torso straight as you swing your leg backward as far as you can, then swing it forward. Complete for the set number of reps.

name: Running Arm Circles
description: Skip forward and swing your arms around in circles forward, then backward.

name: Low Lateral Squat
description: Begin in a wide-legged stance. Shift your weight to one side, bending that knee to descend into a deep squat. Stand back up into the starting position, then shift your weight to the other side. Complete for the set number of reps.

name: Lunge with Rotation
description: Step forward into a lunge, then rotate your torso to face the left, then rotate to face the right. Push up off your back leg to stand again. Step forward into a lunge with the other leg, and repeat.

name: Reverse Lunge with Reach
description: Step backward into a lunge, then reach up with the arm on the same side of your back leg. Reach up and over your body to feel a stretch through your side. Push up with your front leg into a standing position, then repeat on the opposite side.

name: Star Jumps
description: Begin in a crouched position, then jump up and extend all of your limbs at the same time. When you land, immediately drop back into the crouched position, then repeat the jumps for the set number of reps.

name: Quad Stretch w/ Toe Raise
description: Lift one leg and grab your foot, bringing it toward your rear to stretch your quad. Rest your other hand on your hip, then stand up on your toes. Hold for 1-2 seconds, then release and repeat on the other side. Continue alternating for the designated time.

name: Frankensteins
description: Take a step forward, then kick the opposite leg toward your opposte outstretched arm. Release back down, then repeat on the other leg as you walk forward.

name: Scorpions
description: Begin on your stomach with your arms in a T-shape. Bring your heel up toward your opposite arm, twisting your torso up but keeping your chest on the ground. Release to the ground and repeat on the other side.

name: Hip Circles
description: Stand with your hands on your hips. Circle your hips clockwise, then counterclockwise.

name: Lateral Lunge with Arm Raise
description: Holding a resistance band, step out into a lateral lunge. As you descend into the lunge, bring your arms up over your head and pull against the resistance band. Release and go back to standing, then repeat on the other side.

name: Trunk Sidebending with Arm Raise
description: Stand feet shoulder-width apart. Hold the resistance band and raise your arms over your head. Pull against the resistance as you bend to one side. Hold for 1-2 seconds, then release and repeat on the other side.

name: Squats with Toe Raise
description: Stand feet slightly wider than shoulder-width. Squat with proper form then stand back up and go onto your toes. Repeat for the designated reps.

name: Jumping Lunges
description: Begin in a lunged position. Jump up, then switch legs before you hit the ground. Continue to jump and switch legs with every rep.

name: Side to Side Squat
description: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. Perform a squat but shift your weight onto one side so your body is off-center. Come back to the starting position, then perform the squat on the other side. Repeat for the designated reps.

name: Tricep Dips
description: Place your hands on a box, feet on the ground as you hold your self up. Bend your elbows and allow your body to descend. Only use your arms to lift your body back up. Complete for the designated reps.

name: Elevated Pushups
description: Get into a pushup position with your hands on an elevated surface, ideally a box or bench. Perform a pushup regularly, keeping your back straight and your core tight.

name: A-Skips
description: Skip forward, driving your knee upward and keeping the other leg fully extended. Alternate legs, making sure to let both touch the ground in between skips.

name: B-Skips
description: Skip forward, kicking one leg out and keeping the other leg fully extended. Alternate legs, making sure to let both touch the ground in between skips.

name: Upper Calf Stretch
description: Place toes on an elevated surface (i.e. stair/step) with heels on the floor. Lean forward & keep legs straight to feel a stretch through the back of the lower leg.

name: Downward Dog Calf Stretch
description: In a plank position, raise your hips up and back, then lengthen through your shoulders. Try to press your heels toward the ground to feel a stretch through the back of your lower leg.

name: Kneeling Hamstring Stretch
description: On your knees, extend one leg out in front of you. Bend at the waist and press your heel toward the ground to feel a stretch through the back of your hamstring.

name: Lunging Stretch
description: In a low lunge position, extend through your back leg with your toes on the ground & try to push your heel back towards the ground to feel a stretch through the back of the leg.

name: Standing Hamstring Stretch
description: Stand feet shoulder-width apart and reach down toward your toes, keeping your legs as straight as possible.

name: Single Leg Forward Fold (both sides)
description: In a seated position with legs extended, bend one leg and pull one foot toward you. Reach towards the toes of your extended leg.

name: Pretzel Leg Stretch
description: Lie on your back with your feet on the ground & knees bent. Bring one foot up to rest on the opposite knee, then move your feet closer to your hips to deepen the stretch.

name: Modified Pigeon Stretch
description: On all fours with your forearms on the ground, extend one leg back and inward so your foot reaches toward the opposite side. Sit your hips back to deepen the stretch.

name: Supine Hip Rotation
description: Lay on your back with your feet on the ground and knees bent. Bring one foot up to rest on the opposite knee, then rotate to touch the knee of the other leg to the ground. Rotate the hip by moving your knee toward you and away from you.

name: Leaning Kneeling TFL Stretch
description: Begin in a lunge with one knee on the ground. Bring that knee to your midline, then lean forward to feel a stretch in your hip flexor. Raise your hand over your head and lean toward the opposite side to deepen the stretch

name: Seated Leg Cradle
description: Sit in a cross-legged position. Grasp one leg by holding on to the thigh and lower leg and lift it off the ground to feel a stretch through the glutes.

name: Fire Hydrants
description: On all fours, raise one knee out to the side so your thigh is parallel to the ground; make sure to keep your back and neck straight, hips level, and core engaged through the motion.

name: Lying Hip Abduction (straight leg)
description: Lay on your side with legs stacked and hand on hip. Maintain a straight line from your head to your toes as you lift one leg straight off the ground 2ft, then lower it back down.

name: Toe-Heel Taps
description: Lay on your side with legs stacked. With your top leg, touch your toes to the ground in front of your bottom leg, then touch your heel to the ground behind your bottom leg.

name: Windshield Wipers
description: Lay on your side on a bed or table with your lower legs hanging off. Pull the knee of your top leg toward you and keep it at the same height as you rotate your hips so your foot moves above and below your knee.

name: Straight Leg Lifts
description: On all fours, extend one leg all the way back and lift your leg so it is parallel with the ground and lower it back down. Make sure to keep your core engaged, hips level and don't arch your back as you lift your leg.

name: Weightless Deadlifts
description: Stand feet shoulder-width apart with knees slightly bent. Bend at the waist to reach down toward your toes, then stand up by engaging your glutes to lift your torso and straighten your legs. Make sure to not arch your back.

name: Small Clockwise Circles
description: On your side with one leg lifted off the ground and slightly behind your body, move your leg in small clockwise circles. Maintain a flexed foot so your toes are pointing towards you.

name: Bent-Knee Leg Lifts
description: On all fours, lift your leg with your knee bent so your thigh is parallel with the ground and your toes are pointing toward the sky, then lower it back down. Keep your core engaged, hips level, and don't arch your back as you lift.

name: Leg Lifts
description: Lay on your back and engage your core to lift both legs up until your toes point directly upward. Lower them back down slowly, keeping your core tight. Just before your legs reach the ground, lift your legs back up again.

name: Side V-Ups
description: On your side, rest on one elbow and keep your legs straight as you lift them off the ground toward the sky. Lower your legs and keep your core engaged as you lift them up again.

name: Wall Pec Stretch
description: Stand beside a wall or doorway with one leg in front of the other. Bring one arm up to shoulder height and place the palm and inside of the arm on the wall or doorway. Shift your weight onto your front leg and rotate away from the wall.

name: Ball Row, Rotate, Press
description: Lie on your stomach on a stability ball with your legs extended and toes on the ground.  Row your arms and pinch your shoulder blades. Next, rotate elbows out then press arms out in front of you. Bring hands back to ear level, rotate elbows in, and lower your arms back down to the ground.

name: Push-Up Plus
description: Perform a push-up as normal and at the top, push hands into the floor, raising the center of the torso toward the ceiling, causing the shoulder blades "hug" the rib cage.

name: Ball Scaption, T, Cobra
description: Lie on your stomach on a stability ball with your legs extended and toes on the ground. Lift your arms in front of your body at a 45-degree angle with your thumbs pointed up. Next, move your arms straight out to the side keeping your thumbs up with your arms forming a “T”.  Then move your arms to the sides of your body with your thumbs up and palms facing out.

name: Ball Cobra
description: Lie on your stomach on a stability ball with your legs extended and toes on the ground. Extend your arms in front of the ball, engage your core and contract your glutes. Pinch your shoulder blades together while bringing your arms back to the sides of your body. Return your arms out in front of your body and repeat.

name: SMR Biceps
description: Apply pressure to the regions of tightness and sensitivity in your upper arm. When you find a tender spot, maintain pressure for 30 seconds.

name: SMR Brachialis
description: Apply pressure to the regions of tightness and sensitivity in your upper arm. When you find a tender spot, maintain pressure for 30 seconds.

name: SMR Wrist Flexor/Extensor
description: Apply pressure to the regions of tightness and sensitivity in your forearm. When you find a tender spot, maintain pressure for 30 seconds.

name: static bicep stretch
description: Stand feet shoulder-width apart with arms by your side. Pinch your shoulder blades together while bringing your arms around the side of your body so your palms are facing away from you.

name: wrist extensor stretch
description: Stand feet shoulder-width apart with one arm extended at your side, palm facing in front of you. Rotate your wrist so your palm is facing toward the ground, then extend your wrist so your palm is facing toward from you.

name: wrist flexor stretch
description: Stand feet shoulder-width apart with one arm extended at your side, palm facing in front of you. Rotate your wrist so your palm is facing toward the ceiling, then flex your wrist so your palm is facing away from you.

name: Elbow Flexion (shoulder neutral)
description: Anchor resistance band at foot level and stand in neutral position with resistance band in one hand, palm facing away from you. Slowly curl your extended arm towards you and bring your hand to your chest.

name: Elbow Flexion (Shoulder flexed)
description: Anchor resistance band at shoulder level and stand in neutral position with one arm extended and resistance band in hand, palm facing up. Slowly curl your extended arm to bring your hand toward your face.

name: Wrist Flexion
description: While seated, place one forearm on your leg for support with your hand hanging off the side, palm facing towards the ceiling. With a weight, or object like a water bottle in hand, slowly curl at the wrist to bring palm toward you.

name: Wrist Extension
description: While seated, place one forearm on your leg for support with your hand hanging off the side, palm facing towards the ground. With a weight, or object like a water bottle in hand, slowly extend at the wrist to bring your hand towards you.

name: Supination, Pronation
description: While seated, place one arm on your leg for support with your hand hanging off the side, palm facing towards the ceiling. With a weight in hand, or object like a water bottle in hand, slowly rotate at the wrist so your palm is facing the ground.

name: SMR Triceps
description: Lie on one side with an arm on the floor for support. Place a foam roller under the other arm with your hand behind your head. Slowly roll up and down the length of the back of your arm. If you find a tender spot, hold for 30 seconds. Repeat on other side. Don’t have a foam roller? You can use a tennis ball or water bottle.

name: SMR Shoulder
description: Lie on one side with an arm on the floor for support. Place a foam roller in the middle of your shoulder of your opposite arm and slowly roll up and down the length of your shoulder. If you find a tender spot, hold for 30 seconds. Repeat on other side. Don’t have a foam roller? You can use a tennis ball or water bottle.

name: SMR Pecs
description: Lie face down on the floor with one arm extended. Place a foam roller between your arm and chest. Slowly rotate your body side to side to target your chest. If you find a tender spot, hold for 30 seconds. Repeat on other side. Don’t have a foam roller? You can use a tennis ball or water bottle.

name: Wrist Extension
description: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and one arm extended at your side, palm facing away from you. With your other arm, gently pull your extended hand towards your body to the point of tension in the stretch and release.

name: Wrist Flexion
description: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and one arm extended at your side, palm facing toward you. With your other arm, gently pull your extended hand towards your body to the point of tension in the stretch and release.

name: Active Stretch Lats
description: Kneel in front of a chair, ball, or foam roller and place one arm on top of the object with your thumb pointed up toward the ceiling. Keep the other hand on the ground. Lower your hips back toward your heels and hold stretch for 2 seconds. Return to resting position and repeat.

name: Active Stretch Biceps
description: Sit on the floor with knees bent and arms outstretched behind you. Place your palms flat on the floor and fingers pointed away from your body.  Slowly slide your butt forward towards your feet without moving your hands to feel a stretch in your biceps, shoulder, and chest. Push yourself forward to the point of tension in the stretch, but never bounce or push to a point of pain.  Hold this for 1-2 seconds, then slowly return to your starting position and repeat.

name: Overhead Abdominal Stretch
description: Begin by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and facing forward. Intertwine your fingers and extend your arms overhead, turning your palms up toward the ceiling. Slowly bend to your right to feel a stretch in your obliques. Hold for 2 seconds then return to standing. Then slowly bend to your left.

name: Lower Trunk Rotations
description: Lie on your back with knees bent. Gently rock your knees side to side to feel a stretch in your lower back. Focus on keeping your shoulders and upper back on the ground.

name: Standing Calf Stretch (7*)
description: Stand three feet from a wall and put one foot behind you, ensuring your toes are facing forward. Keep your heel on the ground and place your hands on the wall, bending your front leg and keeping your back leg straight. Hold for 1-2 seconds then repeat.

name: Calf (Soleus) Stretch (26*)
description: Stand about three feet from a wall and put one foot behind you, ensuring your toes are facing forward. Keep your heel on the ground and place your hands on the wall, bending your front leg. Once in this position, bend your back knee but do not let your heel come off the ground. You should feel a stretch deeper in your calf. Hold for 1-2 seconds then repeat.

name: Ankle Stretch and Hold (Away From You) (60*)
display_name: Active Ankle Stretch and Hold (Away From You)
description: Begin seated on the floor or in a chair with one ankle rested on the opposite knee. Grasp the toes and pull your toes down, feeling a stretch through the front of your ankle. Hold for 1-2 seconds then repeat.

name: Raised Calf Stretch(214*)
description: Place toes on an elevated surface (i.e. stair/step) with heels on the floor. Lean forward & keep legs straight to feel a stretch through the back of the lower leg. Hold stretch for 1-2 seconds then repeat.

name: Kneeling Hamstring Stretch(216*)
description: On your knees, extend one leg out in front of you. Bend at the waist and press your heel toward the ground to feel a stretch through the back of your hamstring. Hold stretch for 1-2 seconds then repeat.

name: Lying Crossover Glute Stretch(46*)
description: Begin lying on the floor with both legs extended. Bring your ankle to the opposite knee to assume a "Figure-4" position. Pull the raised leg towards your chest until the stretch is felt through the upper hamstring and glute. Hold stretch for 1-2 seconds then repeat.

name: Seated Spinal Twist Stretch(56*)
description: Begin seated with legs extended in front of you. Cross one leg over the other and place that foot on the other side of the extended leg. Place your elbow on the outside of the bent knee and your other hand on the floor for support. Move into a twist and push your elbow into your knee to deepen the twist. Hold stretch for 1-2 seconds then repeat.

name: Leg Cradle(225*)
description: Sit in a cross-legged position. Grasp one leg by holding on to the thigh and lower leg and lift it off the ground to feel a stretch through the glutes. Hold stretch for 1-2 seconds then repeat.

name: Standing Quads Stretch(118*)
description: Stand tall, holding onto a chair or wall for balance if necessary (not pictured). Keep your feet hip-width apart, your back straight and your feet parallel. Reach back and grab your left foot in your left hand to feel a stretch through your quad. Hold stretch for 1-2 seconds then repeat.

name: Wall Pec Stretch(238*)
description: Stand beside a wall or doorway with one leg in front of the other. Bring one arm up to shoulder height and place the palm and inside of the arm on the wall or doorway. Shift your weight onto your front leg and rotate away from the wall. Hold stretch for 1-2 seconds then repeat.

name: Leaning Kneeling TFL Stretch(224*)
description: Begin in a lunge with one knee on the ground. Bring that knee closer to your midline, then lean away from the knee on the ground to feel a stretch in your hip flexor. Hold stretch for 1-2 seconds then repeat.
